1. Install grails 1.3.7 http://grails.org/download/archive/Grails

2. Install git http://git-scm.com/book/en/Getting-Started-Installing-Git

3. Go to grails home directory
	a. git clone https://github.com/strandls/biodiv.git
	b. cd biodiv; grails upgrade

4. Install postgresql http://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/Detailed_installation_guides 
        a. sudo apt-get install postgresql
        b. sudo apt-get install postgresql-client
        c. sudo apt-get install pgadmin3
        d. sudo -u postgres psql postgres
            # \password postgres
        e. createdb biodiv

5. Install postGIS
        a. /etc/init.d/postgresql stop
        b. apt-get install postgresql-9.1-postgis

6. Run following to make biodiv a spatially enabled database.
    a. createlang plpgsql biodiv;
    b. pslq -d biodiv -f /usr/share/postgresql/9.1/contrib/postgis-1.5/postgis.sql
    c. pslq -d biodiv -f /usr/share/postgresql/9.1/contrib/postgis-1.5/spatial_ref_sys.sql

7. Run application 
    a. cd ~/git/biodiv
    b. grails run-app

8. Setting for development on local machine
    sudo vim /etc/hosts
    127.0.0.1       indiabiodiversity.localhost.org localibp
    127.0.0.1       thewesternghats.indiabiodiversity.localhost.org localwbp

9. Setting the host configuration 
    sudo ln -s ~/git/biodiv/app-conf/apache-virtualhost-conf /etc/apache2/sites-available/
    sudo ln -s ~/git/biodiv/app-conf/apache-virtualhost-conf /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/
    sudo a2enmod proxy
    sudo a2enmod rewrite
    edit ~/git/biodiv/app-conf/apache-virtualhost-conf and change DocumentRoot to your dataDir
    sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

8. Loading species pages using script
	
